## Germplasm Phenotype:
   - [clps3-1]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Homozygous clps3-1 mutants cannot be generated. Reciprocal crosses using the gametes from a clps3-1 heterozygote indicate that wild-type and clps3-1 pollen are equally efficient in fertilizing wild type plants. But, there is roughly a 50% reduction in transmission of the clps3-1 mutant female gametophyte. No embryo development can be observed in a presumed homozygote indicating lethality at a very early stage after fertilization. Expression of 35S:CLPS3:TAP rescues the embryo lethality phenotype.
